Characteristics[MaterialType]: About 10 mg frozen tissue per sample
Characteristics[AlkylationReagent]: 40 mM chloroacetamide
Cysteine carbamidomethylation was set as fixed modification
Comment[Instrument]: Q-Exactive HF Orbitrap mass spectrometer (Thermo Scientific)
Comment[Separation]: nanoflow reverse phase liquid chromatography (Dionex Ultimate 3000, Thermo Scientific)
PicoFrit analytical column (75 μm ID × 55 cm long, 15 µm Tip ID (New Objectives, Woburn, MA, USA) in-house packed with 3-µm C18 resin (Reprosil-AQ Pur, Dr. Maisch, Ammerbuch-Entringen, Germany).
Comment[FractionationMethod]: fractionated by strong cation exchange (SCX) chromatography.
Comment[PrecursorMassTolerance]: a mass tolerance of 4.5 ppm for precursor
Comment[NumberOfMissedCleavages]: A maximum of two missed cleavages was allowed for the tryptic digest.
Comment[IonizationType]: Nanoelectrospray was generated by applying 3.5 kV.
Characteristics[NumberOfSamples]: Proteome and metabolome profiles of 19 pRCC and patient-matched healthy kidney controls
